quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,59,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people. He said, “O my people! Worship God—you have no other god except Him. I truly fear for you the torment of a tremendous Day.”"
  7,60,"But the chiefs of his people said, “We surely see that you are clearly misguided.”"
  7,61,"He replied, “O my people! I am not misguided! But I am a messenger from the Lord of all worlds"
  7,62,conveying to you my Lord’s messages and giving you ˹sincere˺ advice. And I know from God what you do not know
  7,63,"Do you find it astonishing that a reminder should come to you from your Lord through one of your own, warning you, so you may beware and perhaps be shown mercy?”"
  7,64,"But they rejected him, so We saved him and those with him in the Ark, and drowned those who rejected Our signs. They were certainly a blind people"